e, Miguel Cané [padre], Eduarda Mansilla y Santiago Estrada) hasta ahora poco consideradas, indagando en la forma en que ponen en escena un determinado modo vital, así como en la pragmática de su producción y recepción, su importancia como objeto material y su función en el escenario mediático emergente.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertVervuert Complete eBook-Package 2021z9783110743340oZDB-207-IBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.31819/978396869073540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783968690735423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783968690735.jpg  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-207-IBVb2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DKUb2021